-tag">&lt;/sup&gt;</span>C (<span class="html-tag">&lt;/font&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;i&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;font <span class="html-attribute-name">face</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">Arial</span>"&gt;</span>thanks to</td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="117"></td><td class="line-content"><span class="html-tag">&lt;a <span class="html-attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="html-attribute-value html-external-link" target="_blank" href="http://blog.tynemouthsoftware.co.uk/" rel="noreferrer noopener">http://blog.tynemouthsoftware.co.uk/</a>"&gt;</span>Dave Curran<span class="html-tag">&lt;/a&gt;</span> for his guidance </td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="118"></td><td class="line-content">and code on this) <span class="html-tag">&lt;/font&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/i&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;font <span class="html-attribute-name">face</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">Arial</span>"&gt;</span>supports low (100KHz) and high (400KHz) speed clocks or higher </td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="119"></td><td class="line-content">(1MHz or more easily achievable).<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span></td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="120"></td><td class="line-content"><span class="html-tag">&lt;b&gt;</span>Hardware:<span class="html-tag">&lt;/b&gt;</span> Very low cost - two chips - ATmega328 and 74HCT166<span class="html-tag">&lt;/font&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span></td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="121"></td><td class="line-content"><span class="html-tag">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;b&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;font <span class="html-attribute-name">face</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">Arial</span>"&gt;</span>Keyboard and serial controller specification:<span class="html-tag">&lt;/font&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/b&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span></td></tr><tr><td class="lin